				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: EQ2 and eqdiva<a name="69209"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 8 04 7:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I crafted a lot, actually.  But right at the end, they made a LOT of changes, including some that made it a pain in the butt.  They also had bugs in that last patch that made some things impossible.  They fixed them, but I didn't do anything after that.  Mostly I didn't because beta was almost over, and I just wasn't motivated to do anything more.
<br />

<br />
The crafting system is complex and interesting.  It can most definitely be a grind though.  You have to want to make the stuff.  The good part is, that player-crafted stuff IS most definitely better than any vendor stuff, and better than common drops.  Named mob drops are generally a little better than common crafted stuff.
<br />

<br />
There are also rare components that you can harvest, which allow you to make REAL nice crafted stuff.  These also require mob-dropped recipe books, and are indeed pretty rare.
<br />

<br />
In general, the heirarchy of stuff goes something like this:
<br />

<br />
Vendor = common mob drop
<br />
Common Crafted
<br />
Quested
<br />
Rare / Named Drops
<br />
Rare Crafted
<br />
Hard / Long Quested
<br />
Raid Drops
<br />
Crafted from Raid Dropped components</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
